== Couscous ==

Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Put the @couscous{120%g} in a #bowl{}.

Pour the @water for the couscous{320%ml} into the bowl and cover tightly with
#cling film{}. Leave to the side for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

== Toasted Almonds ==

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @flaked almonds{15%g} and dry-fry, stirring frequently,
until lightly toasted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Transfer the toasted almonds to a small bowl and set aside.

== Lamb Stew ==

Pop the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat and add the
@lamb mince{200%g}(no oil).

Cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks,
then drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @apricots{}. Add the @chicken stock paste{20%g},
@harissa paste{50%g}, apricots, @tomato passata{1%400g can} and
@water for the sauce{100%ml} to the lamb. Bring to the boil and stir together.

> Add less harissa paste if you don't like heat.

Lower the heat to medium and simmer until the sauce has thickened,
~{6-8%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once thickened, stir the @baby spinach{100%g} into the stew a handful at a
time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Serving ==

When ready, fluff up the couscous with a #fork{}. Taste and season with @salt{}
and @pepper{} if necessary. Share the couscous between your plates, then top
with the stew and a sprinkling of toasted almonds. Enjoy!